===Noun===
'''Sodalite'''

#A [[mineral]] of alkaline [[igneous]] and [[plutonic]] [[rock]]s that are low in [[silica]]. Pink Sodalite is sometimes called ''Hackmanite''. Sodalite and [[Lazurite]] form the ''Sodalite Group'' of silicate minerals.

=== Chemical composition ===
*Sodium aluminum silicate with chlorine, <math>Na_4Al_3Si_3O_{12}Cl</math>
 
